.TH MLP_COPIES "" "" "Environmental Variable"
.PC "Set default number of copies to print"
.PP
When the command
.B lp
spools a job for printing, it reads the environmental variable
.B MLP_COPIES
to find how many copies are to be printed.
The default is one copy; the maximum is 99.
.SH "See Also"
.Xr "environmental variables," environva
.Xr "lp," lp
.Xr "lpadmin," lpadmin
.Xr "lpsched," lpsched
.Xr "printer" printer
